<br>
** BR quest Part ONE **<br>
<br>
Talk to Lon the Redeemed who is in the Temple of Solusek Ro.<br>
He will ask you to collect two Gems and return them to Ortallius in South Ro.<br>
<br>
First Gem:<br>
To get the Gem of Stamina you need to talk to Lon the Redeemed and he will hand you a note which he wants you to give to Conium Darkblade in Dagnors Cauldron.<br>
Hand the Note to Conium Darkblade on the island thats in the middle of the lake. Conium will reward you with an axe labeled &quot;Never Stop Chopping&quot;.<br>
Now head to Highpass Hold. Go to the LumberYard. Talk to Bryan wo is on the second floor on the outside deck and say to him: &quot;Never stop chopping&quot;. NOTE: Keep a general inventory slot open before you say anything to Bryan.<br>
<br>
Give Bryan the Axe labeled &quot;Never Stop Chopping&quot;, in return you recieve a container which he wants you to fill with 10 different drinks.<br>
<br>
The 10 Drinks:<br>
* Underfoot Triple Boch -- Kaladim, Tumpy Irontoe<br>
* Tunare's Finest       -- Felwithe, Wela Muselender<br>
* Vasty Deep Ale        -- Sister Island, Ocean of Tears<br>
* Lendel's Grand Lager  -- Rivervale, Mac Deeppockets<br>
* Gator Gulp Ale        -- East Commons, Bubar<br>
* Frozen Toe Rum        -- Halas, Scon McDaniel<br>
* Oblong Bottle (no drop) -- minus 1611 and 2924 in OOT<br>
* Blood Spirits (no drop) -- Hemo Enologist in courtyard MM<br>
* Clockwork Oil Stout   -- Clockwork CX, Solusek's Eye<br>
* Blackburrow Swig      -- Made yourself.<br>
    Blackburrow Cask<br>
      4 Blackburrow Gnoll Skin<br>
      2 Gnoll pup Scalp<br>
      2 Ol' Tujums Fierce Brew<br>
      (combine these ingredients in the Blackburrow Cask)<br>
<br>
Put all of the above drinks in the box you recieved from Bryan and hit COMBINE.<br>
Once you combine the above you will have a &quot;Box of Spirits&quot;<br>
<br>
Go to Highpass Hold and give the &quot;Box of Spirits&quot; to Bryan McGee. In return you will recieve a Gem of Stamina.<br>
<br>
**** Now take a breather. You earned it and your only half way through this very difficult Quest. ****<br>
<br>
<br>
** BR quest Part TWO **<br>
<br>
Second Gem:<br>
To get the Gem of Rightousness you need to talk to Noresa Sparkle in West Commons. She asks you to save her from Kizdean Gix. She also mentions a Gem Case, which needs 2 keys to open, and that all 3 items (Gem case, and two keys) should be returned to their original crafter to find whats inside.<br>
<br>
Kizdean Gix is in West Commons between the Toll Booth and the INN. Kill him, loot the corpse and you will have a note written in Goblin, telling you about a Dark Elf outcast who stole a sparkling purse.<br>
Head to Solusek's Eye and deep in the dungeon you will kill Lynada the Exhiled who is in the High Shaman room and loot the corpse for the &quot;Sparkling Purse&quot;. this is a 3 hour spawn time for Lynada the Exhiled.<br>
<br>
Return the purse to Noresa Sparkle and she gives you one of the keys needed to open the Gem Case.<br>
The Gem Case is hidden behind a locked door in the slums of East Freeport. The door is locked and you must pick-lock it open. You need a skill level of atleast 120 to open the door.<br>
It is also guarded by a dog named Scrapps.<br>
<br>
Now head to the Freeport Sewers and find Toxdil. Talk to him about the Gem Case and gems. He tells you that he has the second key you need but will only give it to you for the Sparkling Sapphire, which used to be in the Gem Case, but now is in the hands of Noresa Sparkle.<br>
Head to West Commons and buy the Sapphire she has for sale. You will know it's the one it looks like the other Gem you have, and is VERY expensive. Prepare to have 500p with high Charisma, or 700p with about 60 charisma.<br>
&lt;wince&gt; yea thats alot and it hurts the pocket.<br>
<br>
Return the Sapphire to Toxdil and he gives you the second key necessary to open the Gem Case.<br>
Head to East Commons and in the tunnel find Bubar.<br>
Hand the 2 keys and the Gem Case ot Bubar. He will open it for you and give you the Gem of Rightnousness.<br>
Now don't freak out like I did, the second Gem was labeled the same as the Sapphire you bought from Noresa. (I went Balistik). But I assure you it is the second Gem of Rightousness.<br>
<br>
Head to South Ro. Hand the Gem of Stamina, and the Gem of Rightousness (may be labeled Sapphire but looks like the other gem), To Ortalliuos.<br>
He will reward you with the Burning Rapier.<br>
<br>
Mintiky completed this quest at lvl 24.<br>
*Died doing this quest 4 times.<br>
*Recruited Madjake and Wolflilly to guide her and Kill the Spawn in Solusek's Eye.<br>
*Did not kill Kizdean Gix, only looted the note.<br>
*Recruited a High level Paladin to kill the Hemo Enologist, with Forrestt Grummp to heal and Evac.<br>
*Mintiky was camped near and just looted the blood, was killed afterwards but snuck in to drag the corpse and the no drop blood to safety, from MM.<br>
All the rest was easy. Just prepare for ALOT of headache.<br>
The Burning Rapier still does not Process at lvl 27. I'm told it does at lvl 29.<br>
